            "name": "Tinker",
            "range": {
              "range": 60,
              "subtype": "range",
              "text": "range of 60 feet",
              "type": "stat_block_section",
              "unit": "feet"
            },
            "saving_throw": [
              {
                "dc": 5,
                "save_type": "Flat Check",
                "subtype": "save_dc",
                "text": "DC 5 flat check",
                "type": "stat_block_section"
              }
            ],
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "A group of six jinkins can work together for an hour to imbue an item with a curse at a range of 60 feet. While this process is lengthy, it's also unobtrusive and can be performed while Hiding. Jinkins prefer to use this ability on magic items. The curse makes the item unreliable (DC 5 flat check or waste any action to Interact with or Activate the item), adds a bizarre requirement to use the item, or imparts some other curse of a similar caliber.",
            "traits": [
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "remastered",
                  "aonid": 566,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "5c4ada7e08838a63cdcd0d80ecc9c0e7",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "alt": "magical",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "name": "magical",
                    "type": "link"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "Curse",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 630,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "A curse is an effect that places some long-term affliction on a creature. Curses are always magical and are typically the result of a spell or trap. Effects with this trait can be removed only by effects that specifically target curses.   \n  \nAfflictions with this trait are manifestations of potent ill will. A curse either lasts a specified amount of time or can be removed only by certain actions a character must perform or conditions they must meet. A curse with stages follows the rules for afflictions. (_Gamemastery Guide_ pg. 251)",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "remastered",
                  "aonid": 676,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "e96c6783f38a842d8fbd4231a853c319",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "alt": "magical",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "name": "magical",
                    "type": "link"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "Primal",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 635",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 635",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 635,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "e15261ef9d67eae23579ccf106d27c86",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Transmutation",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 637,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the transmutation school of magic, typically changing something\u2019s form.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
